      GET  /results         ΓÇö last sweep results
      POST /endpoint?path=  ΓÇö probe a single endpoint
    
    How it works:
      1. Discovers all routes from OpenAPI spec
      2. Sends lightweight HTTP probe with X-Genesis-Test header (no metric pollution)
      3. Classifies: ACTIVE (2xx), DORMANT (timeout), BROKEN (5xx/connection failed)
      4. Every probe tagged with Genesis key for full provenance
      5. Broken items sent to consensus engine ΓÇö all models diagnose + propose fix
      6. If ALL models agree (Kimi + Opus + Qwen + DeepSeek) with >60% confidence
         ΓåÆ auto-execute healing via diagnostic engine
      7. If disagreement ΓåÆ logged for human review in Dev tab
    
    LLM model probing:
      - Sends 'Reply with PROBE_OK' to each model individually
      - Shows which models are actually callable vs broken vs not configured
      - Exposes the REAL reason models aren't in consensus (API key missing,
        Ollama not running, wrong model name, network timeout, etc.)
    
    Dev tab ΓÇö new Probe Agent panel:
      - 'Probe All APIs' button ΓÇö sweep all routes
      - 'Probe All LLMs' button ΓÇö test each model individually
      - 'Probe ΓåÆ Diagnose ΓåÆ Heal' button ΓÇö full automated pipeline
      - Color-coded model status cards (green/red/yellow/grey)
      - Consensus diagnosis display with agreement/disagreement indicators
    
