    memory mesh feed ΓåÆ LearningExample INSERT with raw Python dicts in
    parameter slots ΓåÆ sqlite3.ProgrammingError: type 'dict' is not supported
    ΓåÆ session poisoned ΓåÆ PendingRollbackError on every subsequent operation.
    
    LAYER 1 ΓÇö File watcher (stop the firehose):
      Added 30+ hard-ignore path fragments: AppData, mozilla, firefox,
      chrome, cache2, Cache, Temp, .tmp, BrowserMetrics, CrashReports,
      Recycle.Bin, thumbnails, fontconfig, dconf, pulse, snap, flatpak.
      These fire before any pattern matching ΓÇö immediate return.
    
    LAYER 2 ΓÇö LearningExample model (fix the column types):
      Changed input_context, expected_output, actual_output, example_metadata
      from Column(JSON) to Column(Text). SQLite's JSON adapter cannot
      reliably bind Python dicts. Text columns with explicit json.dumps()
      are deterministic.
      Added @validates hooks that auto-serialize any dict/list to JSON string.
    
    LAYER 3 ΓÇö LearningPattern model (same fix):
      Changed preconditions, actions, expected_outcomes, supporting_examples
      from Column(JSON) to Column(Text) with @validates serialization.
    
    LAYER 4 ΓÇö Episode model (same fix):
      Changed action, outcome, predicted_outcome, episode_metadata from
      Column(JSON) to Column(Text) with @validates serialization.
      record_episode() now explicitly calls _to_json_str() on all dict params.
    
    LAYER 5 ΓÇö All consumers (handle both formats):
      _contexts_similar(), _outputs_similar(), _extract_common_* all now
      parse stored JSON strings back to dicts via _from_json_str() before
      calling .keys(). This prevents AttributeError on stored strings.
      genesis_key_service uses _sqlite_json_safe() on all JSON columns.
      memory_mesh_integration uses _safe_dict() at the boundary.
    
    The trust_score query bug (WHERE trust_score > {}) was caused by
    _ensure_dict returning {} and leaking into a filter ΓÇö fixed by ensuring
    _ensure_dict is only called on data fields, never on numeric params.
    
