    fix: Genesis key ΓåÆ Memory Mesh dict-to-SQLite crash ΓÇö comprehensive JSON sanitization
    
    Root cause: Python dicts with non-serializable values (datetime objects,
    custom types, nested callables) were being passed through the chain:
      genesis_key_service ΓåÆ memory_mesh_integration ΓåÆ learning_memory ΓåÆ SQLite
    SQLite's JSON columns can't adapt raw Python dicts that contain
    non-JSON-serializable types, causing InterfaceError/ProgrammingError.
    
    Fixed at THREE boundaries:
    
    1. genesis_key_service.py ΓÇö GenesisKey creation:
       - All JSON columns (input_data, output_data, context_data, tags,
         metadata_ai) now pass through _sqlite_json_safe() before insertion
       - Falls back to str() for any non-serializable values
       - Memory mesh feed now uses _safe_json() instead of json.dumps()
    
    2. cognitive/learning_memory.py ΓÇö LearningExample creation:
       - Added _ensure_dict() static method that coerces any value to a
         JSON-safe dict (handles str, dict, None, and arbitrary types)
       - ingest_learning_data() now sanitizes learning_data, input_context,
         expected_output, actual_output before touching the DB
       - _calculate_outcome_quality() and _calculate_consistency() now call
         _ensure_dict() on inputs to prevent .keys() on strings
    
    3. cognitive/memory_mesh_integration.py ΓÇö Episode creation:
       - Replaced basic json.loads() with _safe_dict() that handles all edge
         cases (nested non-serializable, already-a-dict, None, str)
       - _add_to_episodic_memory() now uses _json_safe() for action, outcome,
         predicted_outcome before creating Episode
       - Problem text truncated to 2000 chars to prevent oversized Text columns
    
